# 📊 Customer Churn Detection

## 🌟 Description
Customer churn detection is a machine learning-based project that helps businesses predict which customers are likely to stop using their services. By analyzing historical data and identifying patterns, this project enables companies to take proactive measures to retain customers and improve customer satisfaction.

## 🛠️ Technologies Used
- Python
- Pandas, NumPy (Data Processing)
- Matplotlib, Seaborn (Data Visualization)
- Scikit-Learn (Machine Learning)
- Jupyter Notebook (Development & Analysis)

## 🚀 Features
- 📌 Data Preprocessing: Handles missing values, feature encoding, and data scaling.
- 📊 Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA): Visualizes customer behavior and trends.
- 🔍 Machine Learning Models: Implements algorithms like Logistic Regression, Decision Trees, and Random Forest to predict churn.
- 📈 Model Evaluation: Uses accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score to evaluate model performance.
